# Weather Application - Setup and other info
## Packages needed to run this project
- node
- npm
- sqlite3


## Running the project

### Server
- Open new terminal
- Navigate to the /server folder
- *node index.js*

### Client
- Open new terminal
- Navigate to /client folder
- *npm run dev*


## How it works

### The database
    When the server is running, the weather API is polled every 5 minutes. Each reading is saved to the sqlite database (weather.db). When you open the client, the last 24 readings will be shown, and then every time a new data point is polled, it is added live onto the graph using the publish-subscribe pattern


